  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a large frying pan over a high heat. Drizzle in some olive\noil, then empty the passata straight into the pan. Add 1–2\ntbsp of chipotle paste (to your taste), then pick out the\nroasted peppers with a fork, leaving their juices behind, and tear\ninto the pan. Give everything a stir and season with salt and black\npepper. Let bubble away for 1 minute."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Crack the eggs into the pan and season with salt and black\npepper, then cover with a lid. Cook for 4–5 minutes, until the\nwhites are just set but the yolks are still runny."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, toast the pitta breads, tear into pieces and put into\na serving bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the eggs are cooked, dollop over spoonfuls of the natural\nyogurt, scatter over the parsley and serve at the table with extra\nblack pepper and the pitta breads for dunking."
    }
  ],
